freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Tuesday-Thusday had individual and intermittent pain at shoulders, back, diaphragm,  intestines,  possibly due to gas in intestines.  Some loose stools and slept more than my usual.  At times it felt like an inflating balloon inside, sharp pains.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: 3 times heavy medicine taste on the tongue. Tastes like Iodine smells.  A feeling in intestines that a bowl movement is needed, but there was only excessive gas.  Arm pain dimished when there was a bowel movement as did the taste on the tongue.  Plenty of water also helped with both issues.  The arm pain was more pronounced during evening into early hours of the morning .
Lightheaded a few minutes after vaccine, water and extra minutes wait helped
